 maternal effect coefficient evolves towards negative values in the long
 time limit, because this leads to low values of the phenotypic variance,
 
\begin_inset Formula $\sigma_{z}^{2}$
\end_inset

, and hence to greater population mean fitness.
 Strikingly, in the maternal-environmental case the maternal effect coefficient
 evolves towards zero in the long time limit, which is to be expected because
